details.description:
Welcome to Kunu Coffee Cornelius, your go-to Cornelius neighborhood cafe. We're here to spread positive vibes around Lake Norman, NC through artisanal coffee and tea. Our baristas make every drink with precision, using only the highest quality, ethically-sourced beans, locally sourced A2 milk and organic syrups.
Located on West Catawba in the heart of Cornelius, NC. Whether you're working remote or need a place to bring the kids, our Cornelius cafe swing by for a coffee to start your weekday morning or brighten up your weekend.

raw_data.typical_time_spent: People typically spend up to 1.5 hours here

reviews_data.review_text: By far our favorite coffee spot in town. The owners and staff are friendly and courteous and the coffee, espresso drinks and pastries are top notch.

Really great drinks, great qualify, and some ubique stuff which i enjoy. They serve onyx coffee. Beautiful space, very very busy. It was quite a long wait. I had planned to go hang out and by the time I got my order in I had to change it cuz i had to leave. But I wanted to stay cuz It was a cumplir environment (it was their morning rush though so keep that in consideration). Nice people and delicious drink though!

review_questions.null: Dietary restrictions, Parking, Kid-friendliness, Wheelchair accessibility

reviews_data.owner_answer: Thank you for your review, Rebekah! We appreciate your feedback and sincerely apologize for the longer-than-expected wait for your drink. We're continuously working to improve our processes, especially during busy hours. For added convenience, we offer a mobile app that allows you to order ahead, helping to minimize wait times when you're on the go. We hope to serve you again soon!

reviews_data.review_text: Great coffee and service!
reviews_data.owner_answer: Thanks for taking the time to review us Derek. We're here to serve our community in the best way we can.

reviews_data.review_text: The best coffee in town with the best vibes! Kunu is a block from our house and is the best asset to our neighborhood! We are thrilled to have delicious coffee and even better atmosphere within walking distance. 10/10 recommend ⭐️⭐️⭐️⭐️⭐️
reviews_data.owner_answer: Thanks for mentioning us Hillary. We appreciate all your support!

reviews_data.review_text: I loved the mocha and the vibes here. Definitely my go to now when I’m Cornelius. Customer service was nice as well!
It's cozy inside, and there's also a place to sit outside. It's worth going to see
Very friendly staff and great matcha! Love the atmosphere.
Amazing atmosphere and coffee. First timer from Chicago but really good coffee got the Omc.

I have never been disappointed in the quality of people or the quality of coffee being produced from this establishment. The baristas are the kindest professionals you can find in the area, the attention to detail and care taken to serve the highest quality espresso and drip coffees is unmatched. You can taste the expertise and dedication in each cup! The music permeates the space with a nice sound that you can get lost in while doing work or catching up with friends. Could not be more thankful for what the owners and laborers of Kunu coffee are doing here in this little part of town! Excited to continue supporting local coffee!!

Visited for the first time and loved this place! I got a free drink through their app and will definitely come back to try some of their seasonal flavors. I got the matcha latte which was crafted with care and had a delicious umami flavor. I love that all the mugs and plates are made by a local ceramics artist.
Good coffee. atmosphere is ok: could use some more interesting decor

I like the little chocolate they give with my cappuccino.

Lots of power outlets, seems like a nice place to do work but limited inside seating.
Great coffee and service!
I love coming to Kunu to work or meetup with friends! Their coffee is high-quality and they have the best Chai Tea Latte.

When Kunu opened in my neighborhood I was sooo excited. Their coffees are so unique and I genuinely CRAVE their pumpkin chai. Love that you can order ahead and the owner + staff are always super nice. Highly recommend!

The cold brew was too expensive and watered down, awkward layout, unfriendly cashier but otherwise nice staff.

Strong branding and newly refurbished though
Good mocha. Could have just a little more chocolate for my taste. I'm sure they would have fixed it if I asked. Very nice folks
reviews_data.owner_answer: Thanks for taking the time to review us George! Next time you can definitely ask for some extra chocolate.

reviews_data.review_text: Cute local coffee shop
The lattes were so smooth and delightful, the pumpkin muffin was a perfect fall treat, and the customer service was lovely. Next time I visit the area I will definitely be returning
Great spot. Super cool owner, great coffee.
Cute place with good coffee and good atmosphere
Dog friendly

Great coffee, muffins, atmosphere, and staff. We'll be back soon.
I got the Peach Cobbler Oat Milk Latte and it was better than expected. Unique and well balanced.
Great spot. Very comfortable and awesome people.
Love this little coffee shop a short drive from my condo. Nice outdoor seating and great lattes (my go-to). Staff is always nice and helpful.
Highly recommended!!
Great service and amazing food!
Iced latte tasted strange, and hot coffee wasn't good. Uncomfortable seats. Try another place for coffee.

I can't say enough about Kunu Coffee! It's quaint and cozy, without feeling claustrophobic. I love the little couch seating area with the table that was the perfect height for my toddler to stand at. The lattes were smooth and yummy. Definitely a good place to sit and chill.
Great spot, great coffee
Extremely delicious coffee - great atmosphere, friendly, warm and welcoming staff. I will definitely be back - Highly recommend!
Best coffee in town! Finally somewhere that is different and out of the normal. Quality ✔️
Love the coffee and the staff. ❣️

love the quaintness and community feel as well as the decor.  Had an iced espresso mule which was wonderful!
Worth your while😊
Family friendly environment. Very clean. Very nice people and the drinks are good! Very unique decor.
Awesome coffee shop!

Great location since they are among massive residential for now. Space is ok but really small(no room for big party meeting, better to sit outside decently comfortable. Across Catawba(very busy traffic) is undeveoped for now.

Coffee way too acidic and then smallest cup is $3 with $1min tip request.

Prob not gonna come back nothing great except if you live within waling and dont want to work from home...but no reason to drive here.
The girls who were working were so welcoming and sweet and the energy in there is awesome. Also a few fun books to flip through :)
Great coffee, great customer service.

Great looking coffee shop. Clean modern lake vibe made cozy and interesting with attractive artwork. Love the handmade ceramic cups. This is the kind of place you want to make your second home. A winner!

What a fantastic addition to the local area.  Stopped in yesterday and had a great experience and even better coffee.  All I can say is if your sick of the rat race in the coffee business and the mess of a parking lot and experience down the street...and...if you actually like to TASTE quality, make it a point to stop in here.  Wow!  So good!
High-quality coffee and super friendly staff. It has a great interior, too. I plan on being a regular for sure.

The coffee is great, baked items are yummy too. I have only been a few times so far since they opened, but know I will continue to be stopping in. I love the location and the decor inside the coffeeshop is very nice.
Great coffee, great atmosphere and super friendly service!

Best coffee on Exit 25/28!
This coffeeshop is dedicated to coffee done well, and that's proven and shown through the menu and selection. They bring a laser-focus to coffee, and you can tell that difference when you taste it. The coffees range from floral and delicate to juicy and fruity, and the all smell amazing! Staff is welcoming and hospitable, the gold standard that Kunu has set for the North Charlotte area.
Kunu Cornelius is a great addition to the Kunu family, and I'm so glad they're serving this area. This Kunu location is cozy and intimate, welcoming all who truly love hospitality through good specialty coffee.
